body:
Hi,
  For enums - assigning an int value requires explicit static casting in SV LRM. However many tools relax this and issue a warning. In Icarus this throws an error as below, can you consider demoting it into a warning and do implicit conversion?

The second issue is - type cast is NOT yet supported, so all the more reason to consider this request.

```log
ivl_uvm_i452.sv:8: error: This assignment requires an explicit cast.
1 error(s) during elaboration.
```

```verilog
package t;
   typedef enum {IDLE, APB_WR, APB_RD} apb_kind_e;

  class apb_xn;
    rand apb_kind_e kind;

    function new ();
      kind = $urandom ();
    endfunction : new 

    virtual function void print ();
      $display ("%m kind: %0d ", kind);
    endfunction : print 
  endclass : apb_xn

endpackage

module m;
  import t::*;

  initial begin
    $finish (2);
  end
endmodule 

```

